TITLE: Implementing Split View Resizing with Delta Compensation
DESCRIPTION: This pseudocode demonstrates the algorithm for resizing split view components while maintaining constant width. It introduces a delta () value for left-side adjustments and compensates on the right side to preserve overall width.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mathuo/dockview/blob/master/packages/docs/src/misc/math/math.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: pseudocode
CODE:
```
_remaining = 
_used = 0
for(j = i; j >= 0; i--) do
    V^next_j = Min(V^max_j, Max(V^min_j, V_j + _remaining))
    V^_j = V^next_j - V_j
    _remaining = _remaining - V^_j
    _used = _used + V^_j
    V_j = V^next_j

for(j = i+1; j < n; i++) do
    V^next_j = Min(V^max_j, Max(V^min_j,V_j - _used))
    V^_j = V^next_j - V_j
    _used = _used + V^_j
    V_j = V^next_j
```

