TITLE: Calculating Delta Constraints for Split View Resizing
DESCRIPTION: These formulas calculate the minimum and maximum constraints for the delta () value used in split view resizing. They ensure that view sizes remain within specified limits and maintain overall component width.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mathuo/dockview/blob/master/packages/docs/src/misc/math/math.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: pseudocode
CODE:
```
^min_left =  V^min_j - V_j    j = i,...0
^max_left =  V^max_j - V_j    j = i,...0
^min_right =  V_j - V^min_j    j = i+1...n
^max_right =  V_j - V^min_j    j = i+1...n

_min = MAX ( V^min_left , V^max_right )
_max = MIN ( V^max_left , V^min_right )

_clamped = MIN ( V_max , MAX ( V_min ,  ) )
```

